I"Í<p>In this tutorial we will learn about file operators in Shell Programming by using the <a href="/bash/conditions">if statement</a> to perform tests</p>

<table>
  <thead>
    <tr>
      <th>Operator</th>
      <th>Note</th>
    </tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
    <tr>
      <td>-e</td>
      <td>To check if the file exists.</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>-r</td>
      <td>To check if the file is readable.</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>-w</td>
      <td>To check if the file is writable.</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>-x</td>
      <td>To check if the file is executable.</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>-s</td>
      <td>To check if the file size is greater than 0.</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>-d</td>
      <td>To check if the file is a directory.</td>
    </tr>
  </tbody>
</table>

